The festival kicks off on Friday. CAPE TOWN - Knysna Tourism says the town is ready to host the upcoming Pick 'n Pay Knysna Oyster Festival.May fires destroyed over 300 B&amp;B establishments in the Southern Cape Town.Changes have also been made to the Featherbed Trail Run event as a result of the blaze.Seven people died and thousands others had to flee their homes when the fire broke out.Knysna Tourism PR Manager Jeannine Orzechowshi said: We have a lot of people coming in to enjoy the festival. In terms of the damage to Kynsna, most of the tourists' activities and accommodation establishments were not damaged. We did get some damage to some guesthouses and B&amp;Bs but we have at least 4,000 beds available. The festival kicks off on Friday.